Q: A man spend 810 in buying trouser at Rs 70 each and shirt at 30 each. What will be the ratio of trouser and shirt when the maximum number of trouser is purchased?
Options: (a) 9 Trousers (b) 8 Trousers (c) 10 Trousers (d) 7 Trousers (e) 11 Trousers
A:
 Let the number of trousers be x. Then, the number of shirts will be (810 - 70x)/30. The number of trousers will be maximum when the number of shirts is minimum, i.e., when (810 - 70x)/30 is 1. 810 - 70x = 30 810 = 70x + 30 780 = 70x 12 = x. So, the answer is (d). 12 Trousers. (Note: The question is asking for the ratio of trousers and shirts, not the number of trousers. So, the answer is 12:1 or 12/1.) Q: A
